 collars jobs, are driven to help the tens of millions of people who use their bodies as instruments for productivity daily.','Tell us about you and your team','Anything else you want to share?','Venture Funding','Prototyping shops','Why do you want to be at New Lab?','2016-04-22 19:05:17','2016-04-22 19:05:17'),(571,'2016-04-21','Stephan','DeBaets','lilly@newlab.com','Chef\'s Club','http://www.chefsclub.com/','','','Small: 5-9','Life Sciences','Resident','Cafe','Use this space if you\'d like to tell us more about your technology','Tell us about you and your team','Anything else you want to share?','Self-Sustaining','Member Community','Why do you want to be at New Lab?','2016-04-22 19:05:17','2016-04-22 19:05:17'),(572,'2016-04-21','Matthew','Putman','lilly@newlab.com','Nanotronics Imaging','http://www.nanotronics.co/','','','Medium: 10-30','Nano Technology','Resident','Combining optical microscopy, computational super-resolution, artificial intelligence, and robotics, Nanotronics is bringing the world’s most advanced microscope to every manufacturing sector. \r\n\r\nWe automate industrial microscopes used for inspection of the world\'s most advanced technologies: semiconductors, microchips, hard drives, LEDs, aerospace hardware, nano-fillers, nanotubes, nano-medicine, and more. Our microscopes are an','Use this space if you\'d like to tell us more about your technology','Tell us about you and your team','Anything else you want to share?','Venture Funding','Prototyping shops','Why do you want to be at New Lab?','2016-04-22 19:05:17','2016-04-22 19:05:17'),(573,'2016-04-24','Ashley','Adewuyi','ashley@liloe.co','LiLoe Labs','www.hellojeffrie.com','https://www.facebook.com/ihomedelivery/','','Micro: 2-4','Connected Devices','Resident','LiLoE Labs is a home automation company and our first product is Jeffrie, a smart mailbox that allows consumers to receive deliveries and packages safely at their door even when they are not home.  Jeffrie\'s companion app tracks your packages, sends e-shopping deals and grants access to Jeffrie.  ','Jeffrie has a BLE lock and android and iOS apps. Our app is launching first as a standalone product in June.','Ashley Adewuyi – CEO\r\nNavy Intelligence Officer + 10yrs\r\nProgram Management, Rapid Prototyping, Leadership Experience	\r\n\r\nChristian Brown – CTO\r\nIndustrial Designer +15 yrs \r\nMechanical Engineering, Chinese Manufacturing 	\r\n\r\nJamal Gillespie – Software Developer\r\nSoftware Engineer +7yrs \r\nFull Scope Application Developer, UI/UX and designer\r\n  \r\n','We are really excited to enter a new market ripe for disruption with excellent market opportunity. Additionally our startup was chosen to be one of only four companies to participate in their innovative logistic accelerator. This summer we start beta testing the Jeffrie with key strategic partners.\r\n','Venture Funding','Prototyping shops, Member Community','We are new to city and are looking to join a like minded hardware-centric community. Additionally a friend of mine David Droz mentioned the open application and thought we would be good a fit for the community. We have a lot of exciting things going on in the company, such as, celebrity endorsement so we believe that we have a lot to contribute to the community as well.','2016-04-25 03:07:26','2016-04-25 03:07:26'),(574,'2016-04-24','Jonathan ','Schipper','generalmotion@gmail.com','EXOvault','jonathanschipper.com','exovault.com','','Small: 5-9','Connected Devices','Resident','EXOvault is an artist run design and manufacturing company that has been based in Brooklyn for five years.  We produce state of the art eye-ware, cellphone cases and briefcases that blur the line between utilitarian objects and artwork.  Jonathan Schipper is also an active sculptor, showing his work worldwide.','EXOvault produces all its objects via CNC milling machines.  We own four cnc mills and a robot.  We have used the power of digital production to bring manufacturing back to Brooklyn.  We are experts in 3d modeling and computer aided manufacturing. ','We are five artists lead by Jonathan Schipper.  Jonathan has been an artist making kinetic sculptures for 20 years.  He shows internationally and is best know for his slow motion car crash, which simulates a head on collision using real cars and, depending on the duration of the show, taking from three days up to year to collide.  https://jonathan-schipper-cfh7.squarespace.com/config#/pages|/#/car-crash/','EXOvault is losing it\'s space in Greenpoint due to the sale of our building.  We have been running a shared work space with the same goals as New Lab for 5 years.  We provided facilities and equipment for eight engineers artists and designers at a time.  We have a great deal of knowledge and equipment that we would be excited to integrate into New Lab.','Self-Sustaining','Prototyping shops, Member Community','We are strong believers in community technology and we are excited to bring our experience and creative energy to such an important endeavor. \r\n','2016-04-25 03:07:26','2016-04-25 03:07:26'),(575,'2016-04-25','Aditya','Kumarakrishnan','adityak@teslab.co','Teslab','www.teslab.co','www.linkedin.com/in/adityakumarakrishnan','','Micro: 2-4','Additive Tech','Resident','Teslab is a cloud OS for 3D printer farms that is compatible with over 95% of printers and allows for cloud slicing, automatic queuing, remote device control, and multi-user compatibility.  With Teslab, educators can seamlessly integrate 3D printing into classrooms, libraries can open up 3D printing hubs and much more. ','We\'ve developed, from the ground up, the first automatic slicing and queueing system of its kind. You connect all of your 3D printers to Teslab, and it does everything else. Multiple users can submit their 3D designs to Teslab. The designs get automatically routed to printers as they become available and sliced appropriately. Teslab is the only system that allows multiple users to seamlessly control multiple devices.\r\n\r\nView a demo of Teslab at:\r\nmy.teslab.co\r\nUsername: user\r\nPassword: teslab123','Aditya Kumarakrishnan - CEO & Co-Founder\r\nCity University of New York - Queens College\r\nBA Applied Physics, BA Mathematics, Minor: Philosophy \r\nInteresting Fact: Aditya built a mobile maker space in a 22ft Fed-ex step truck with 3D printers, laser cutters, and other CNC machines, that he drove around from school to school reaching over 500 students teaching hands-on science. To make it possible, he raised a total of $125k through sponsorships, competitions and an IndieGoGo campaign (www.teslatruck.co). \r\n\r\nArun Kumarakrishnan - CTO & Co-Founder\r\nCity University of New York - Queens College\r\nBS Computer Science, BA Philosophy, BA Political Science\r\nInteresting Fact: In college, Arun worked extensively on homomorphic encryption and published 3 peer-reviewed papers and 1 book chapter, successfully filed 2 patents, and became the CTO of an NSF-SBIR funded company working on healthcare data - all before his senior year. ','We\'re brothers and this is our second start-up together. In our first, we bootstrapped an educational electronics company to $1M in revenue in 18 months and learned more through that experience than anything else we had ever done - www.16hertz.com. \r\n\r\nIn 16hertz, some of our notable achievements include: \r\n- Hacking the Arduino to create the first sub $15, wifi-enabled, robotics optimized microcontroller that First Robotics (FRC) teams around the world are using on their robots today (https://github.com/adityavkk/Leonardo_PlusPlus)\r\n\r\n- Created the first comic book style, programming, and electronics Arduino guide (have a look - http://bit.ly/illustratedarduino)\r\n','Grants','Prototyping shops, Conference rooms & breakout spaces, Member Community','We\'ve noticed that when we\'re around innovators we tend to innovate. What better group of innovators, specifically in high-tech hardware, than the community at New Lab. We feel like we have so much to learn and share with the community. In addition, the prototyping shops at New Lab will be a tremendous help for us as we are constantly outsourcing our fabrication now. ','2016-04-25 06:45:57','2016-04-25 06:45:57');
